Paper: 0010278
Title: Finite size effects in perturbed boundary conformal field theories
Authors: P. Dorey and M. Pillin and A. Pocklington and I. Runkel and R. Tateo and G. M. T. Watts
Abstract: We discuss the finite-size properties of a simple integrable quantum field theory in 1+1 dimensions with non-trivial boundary conditions. Novel off-critical identities between cylinder partition functions of models with differing boundary conditions are derived.
